(Import [(b2jg ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Constraint [Tests across the nota/schema/sema stack load real separate .nota/.schema/.sema files via a small shared read-fixture helper, never inline source strings. Every .schema fixture is NOTA-legal, parsable by nota-next before lowering, and uses local relative imports. Real file-based tests prove each step: structural parse, the shared nota-next codec, schema-of-schemas read, macro assembly into macro-free Asschema data, the roots model, Rust datatype/derive emission over the shared codec, and the actor system running full constraints on spirit-next.] High High Zero [nota-next schema sema spirit-next asschema])) (js3u ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Decision [|Integration tests exercise the actual execution chain through trait surfaces with per-plane schema-typed values throughout: real .schema files drive Nix codegen; the Nix-built CLI and daemon launch; the CLI sends real rkyv signal frames over a real Unix socket; signal-engine (Signal->Signal), nexus-engine (Nexus->Nexus plus translations), and sema-engine (SEMA->SEMA durable state) process and reply end-to-end. Never bypass the trait surface or collapse typed events to tokens; assert Signal/Nexus/SEMA boundaries were entered through engine methods at runtime, on typed schema-emitted outputs.|] Medium Medium Zero [signal-engine nexus-engine sema-engine rkyv schema trait-surface])) (zze6 ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Correction [Real-world end-to-end testing uses the most real production topology; sandbox shortcuts that omit a load-bearing piece are not e2e. For the message-passing engine, true e2e is a real agent sending a real message to another real agent whose response returns to the first; a routed daemon path ending at a fake terminal or acceptance socket is only a routing-harness witness, not full e2e.] Medium Minimum Zero [message-passing-engine e2e])) (jkkq ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Constraint 