ability) and proves it survives SSH disconnect. The gate accepts an authorized head and rejects an unauthorized one fail-closed, building from 1-of-1 local toward multi-machine quorum.|] High Medium Zero [criome lojix prometheus microvm digital-ocean spirit-gate vmhost])) (y1v5 ([(Technology (Software (Quality Testing)))] Decision [|CriomOS gains a node feature for VM-based testing using the best Linux VM tech: a real display/GPU/DRM-capable VM (headless wlroots lacks wlr-gamma-control), Nix-native, CI-automatable and interactively viewable, to test CriomOS and visual/UI/GPU components end-to-end — launch the real app, run the component, observe the actual visual effect (theme/warmth/brightness) while watching for freezes and errors. chroma is the first target; sandboxes can run via systemd on a node such as Prometheus.|] Medium Minimum Zero [criomos chroma vm-testing prometheus gpu])) (8jtz ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces)))] Correction [Spirit ordinary agent-facing replies should not include database markers; database markers should be returned only by an explicit operation that asks for marker state.] High High Zero [spirit])) (kg2z ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces)))] Correction [|Spirit CLI invocations default to inline NOTA wrapped in shell double quotes; the bracket-string notation keeps NOTA itself double-quote-free so the whole object passes as one shell argument. Temp-file NOTA paths are reserved for genuine need (binary signal-encoded paths, or shell metacharacters too painful to escape) — multi-line context fields are not such a case.|] High Minimum Zero [spirit nota])) (hetk ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces)))] Correction [|Help retrieval is always one NOTA argument: every component supports (Help) / (Help Main) / (Help Verb) and nested forms like (Record (Slot1 (Workspace Help))) in its NOTA vocabulary, never bare-word CLI args. Help docs likely auto-wired via the signal-channel macro.|] High Minimum Zero [spirit nota signal-channel])) (9c6f ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces)))] Decision [|Spirit provides RecordDefault, a short-form recording op taking only commonly-customized fields (topics, kind, description, magnitude) with defaults injected for the rest (privacy Zero/open per dev-mode public-repo grounding, daemon-stamped date/time). Record stays the canonical full-fidelity op; RecordDefault is the daily-use shortcut.|] Medium Minimum Zero [spirit nota])) (ca65 ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces)))] Correction [Skills should instruct agents to use the unsuffixed spirit CLI for normal intent capture; versioned Spirit wrappers are diagnostic or explicit testing surfaces, not the normal agent command.] Medium Minimum Zero [spirit])) (fiw4 ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces)))] Decision [|Versioned CLIs need an active-version selector. Spirit exposes version lookup as the bare NOTA input Version (spirit Version) — not a Unix flag and not a parenthesized empty record.|] Medium Minimum Zero [spirit nota])) (js6b ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces)))] Principle [Trace client behavior belongs in a reusable client library that can enable NOTA display or SEMA-backed trace logging; the CLI should be a thin wrapper around that library.] Medium Minimum Zero [nota sema client-library])) (kfon ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces)))] Decision [|Content-extracting/emitting Spirit operations accept a customizable output-target enum as the final request field — variants Stdout, Stderr, File(path). Stderr is a normal output option, not an error channel. CollectRemovalCandidates uses it; future export/dump ops the same way, keeping the wire interface uniform.|] Medium Minimum Zero [spirit collect-removal-candidates])) (rh29 ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces)))] Constraint [Spirit record acceptance replies should display the shortest collision-free lowercase identifier prefix with a minimum length of four characters, not the full stored identifier.] Medium Minimum Zero [spirit])) (sn1g ([(Technology (Software (Surfaces CommandLineInterfaces))) (Technology (Software (Engineering Architecture)))] Decision [Spirit may expose common search paths as explicit low-level shorthand Signal verbs, with public text lookup named PublicTextSearch rather than forcing agents through the full eight-field Observe query for ordinary public search.] Low Minimum Zero [spirit signal-spirit])) (ahop ([(Work Teamwork)] Decision [|Counselor and assistant pair like designer and operator: counselor advises on structure (the psyche's personal, business, family, friends logistics); assistant executes. The pair handles the psyche's private affairs by default.|] High High Zero [counselor assistant designer operator])) (nytm ([(Work Teamwork)] Decision [|Valid lane shapes: <role>, ordinal second-/third-<role> for parallel capacity (copying the whole following role), and qualified-prefix-<role> (system-, cluster-, pi-). Specialized lanes inherit their base role (system-specialist becomes system-operator). Each agent uses its exact harness role-name; -assistant and -specialist suffixes are retired.|] High High Zero [lane-naming second-role system-operator cluster-operator])) (xlfo ([(Work Teamwork)] Decision [A dispatched subagent inherits the dispatcher's lane, lock, and report-numbering slot — it writes into the dispatcher's role report subdir, never its own lane. Parallel subagents are assigned report numbers before launch; sharing the dispatcher's single lock, two cannot work the same thing.] High Medium Zero [subagent lane lock report-numbering])) (9o9g ([(Work Teamwork)] Constraint [|Report lanes are per-role and divide write authority and research context: an agent writes only in its own reports role directory — except when the psyche explicitly instructs it for one specific task (not normalized after). Reports are exempt from claim flow; claim only for shared coordination surfaces or files outside the exemption.|] High Medium Zero [reports role-lanes claim-flow write-authority])) (jq8w ([(Work Teamwork)] Principle [Designer lanes are different windows into the same persona; share context through workspace files plus per-session work summaries] High Minimum Zero [designer workspace-files session-summaries])) (kxzh ([(Work Teamwork)] Decision [|The per-role psyche-to-agent flow is the role's protocol (designing, operational, poet): when the psyche talks to a role, that conversation designs that role's operating skill. The role label in the window determines which protocol the psyche speaks through; psyche conforms to that interface.|] High Minimum Zero [designer-protocol operator-protocol poet-protocol role-label])) (ty8z ([(Work Teamwork)] Principle [Before dispatching a new subagent the designer first researches what other agents have done since the last pass and what is in flight, to avoid duplicate work and stale-substrate assumptions. Operators read peer operator reports first and watch new designer reports.] High Minimum Zero [designer operator reports cross-lane-research])) (xrxy ([(Work Teamwork)] Decision [|The prime designer chair runs parallel subagent workflows by default (a designer-specific exception to the no-subagents default still binding operator, system, poet, and assistant lanes); it does not extend to second/assistant designer lanes unless the psyche says so. The composite designer runs Claude and Codex in parallel on the same prompt, then selects or merges. Operators use parallel subagents only when authorized, staying responsible for integration, constraints, tests, and the final report.|] High Minimum Zero [prime-designer composite-designer subagents operator claude codex])) (8dib ([(Work Teamwork)] Decision [The primary workspace has a new system-maintainer role: the system maintainer owns mostly updating, debugging, and deploying Crayon OS on various hosts, is 